01 / Philosophy

Brand Philosophy & Statement

From the stillness of deep water, the lotus rises, untouched by the complexity below, always reaching toward light. LookAI is that lotus: a system that sees through the chaos of the software lifecycle and delivers clarity, cycle after cycle, without interruption.

LookAI Brand Statement

The LookAI logo uses two forms from Indian geometry: the mandala and the lotus. The founders chose them not as decoration, but because each is a precise structural analog for what the platform does.

â˜¸

Mandala

A mandala is a closed geometric system that radiates from a single center point. Every ring connects to the one before it and the one after: it does not terminate, it completes. The software development lifecycle works the same way: requirements, architecture, code, testing, deployment, monitoring. A cycle that closes cleanly and begins again.

ðŸª·

Lotus / Padma

The lotus grows in muddy water and delivers a clean result every time. The environment does not affect the quality of what it produces. LookAI takes ambiguous requirements, legacy constraints, and manual processes as inputs, and outputs production-ready, documented, tested code. Every time. Without fail.

âœ¦

The Spark

The center point of the mark is where every pipeline begins: the business requirement. From that single input, every artifact radiates outward: GitHub issues, generated code, QA test suite, release package, in sequence, automatically.

ðŸ”„

The Cycle

The symmetry of the mandala encodes the platform's core behavior: the software lifecycle is autonomous, self-completing, and repeatable. No manual intervention. No lost context between cycles. The same quality of output, every run.

02 / Logo

Logo System

The LookAI wordmark pairs "Look" in confident white with "AI" in Digital Lotus cyan, signaling the distinction between human intent and machine intelligence. The icon, a mandala-lotus in a softly rounded square, can stand alone at small sizes. The two should never be separated from their proportional relationship.

Primary / Dark
Reversed / Light
Icon Only
Clear Space Rule

The minimum clear space around the logo on all sides is equal to the cap-height of the letter "L" in the wordmark. Never place the logo on busy backgrounds, on colors that reduce contrast below 4.5:1, or at sizes where the mandala petals are no longer distinguishable.

02b / Logo System

Two-Logo System

LookAI operates two distinct logo versions. They share the same icon and wordmark treatment but serve different contexts. Using the wrong version in the wrong context is a brand inconsistency. The rules below are not suggestions.

Version 03: Licensed Deployments Only
"Powered by LookAI" Bug

When the LookAI platform is licensed to a third party and deployed under a private label, a compact attribution bug must appear in the product UI. This is a contractual branding requirement and cannot be removed, hidden, or modified by the licensee.

Bug Specification
Placement: Bottom-right of the platform viewport, persistent across all screens
Size: Minimum 80px wide. Must remain legible at 1Ã— pixel density
Text: "Powered by LookAI": exact phrasing, no substitutions
Icon: Mandala mark only (no wordmark). White or Digital Lotus cyan on dark; Indigo Night on light
Contrast: Must meet 4.5:1 contrast ratio against its background
Link: Must link to lookai.studio on click
Permitted Modifications
  • Position adjustment within the bottom-right quadrant
  • Color inversion for light-background UI contexts
Not Permitted
  • Hiding, obscuring, or reducing opacity below 70%
  • Altering the phrasing or removing the icon
  • Placing over content that competes for attention

05 / Voice & Tone

Brand Voice

LookAI speaks with the quiet confidence of something that has already solved the problem. We do not shout. We do not oversell. We illuminate, the way a lamp does not argue with the darkness.

âœ¦ We Are

  • Precise and purposeful, no word wasted
  • Confident without arrogance
  • Grounded in engineering truth
  • Culturally aware, never performative
  • Curious about complexity, serene in delivery

âœ• We Are Not

  • Hype-driven or superlative-heavy
  • Preachy about AI disruption
  • Corporate or bureaucratic in tone
  • Dismissive of human nuance
â˜¸ Clarity over complexity
ðŸª· Rise from the noise

06 / Cultural Grounding

Our Heritage

LookAI was founded by engineers from India. The mandala and lotus in the logo come from that background, and they stayed in the logo because they are structurally accurate representations of what the platform does.

The mandala is a system map. The lotus is a quality guarantee. The center point is the business requirement. Everything the platform produces radiates from it: automatically, reliably, every cycle. That is the promise. That is the brand.

Core Brand Principles
Autonomous
The system runs the cycle. Engineers direct the outcome.
Clarity
Clean output regardless of the complexity of the input.
Repeatable
Same quality every cycle. No variance from run to run.
Complete
The cycle closes. Nothing is handed off incomplete.
